{"lemma":"أَبَدِ","slug":"أَبَدِ","root":"#.ب.د","root_slug":"_-ب-د","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ب-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9","n10","n12","n13","n14","n15","n1942"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"active participle of أَبَدَ (ʔabada)","tags":["active","form-i","form-of","participle"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʔaː.bid/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9","headword_ar":"اَبَدَ","root":"Abd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubuwdN","text_ar":"اُبُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He remained, stayed, abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dwelt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constantly, continually,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"permanently, without quitting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bimakaAnK","text_ar":"بِمَكَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a place;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada","text_ar":"اَبَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"having for its aor."},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada","text_ar":"اَبَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, M, L, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubuwdN","text_ar":"اُبُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, L, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA^b~d","text_ar":"تابّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, M, A, Mgh, L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a beast)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became wild,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sky;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tawaH~a$a","text_ar":"تَوَحَّشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, A, Mgh, L, Msb, K:) [because wild animals live long, unless killed by accident; accord. to what is said by As and others in explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^waAbidN","text_ar":"اوَابِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(sing."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=bidapN","text_ar":"ا=بِدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") applied to animals, as meaning wild:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took fright, and fled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran away at random:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"took fright at, and shunned, mankind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubuwdN","text_ar":"اُبُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shrinking"},{"kind":"text","text":"from a thing, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shunning"},{"kind":"text","text":"it; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nufuwrN","text_ar":"نُفُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Kull pp. 30 and 31.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abida","text_ar":"اَبِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA^b~d","text_ar":"تابّد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became unsocial, unsociable, unfamiliar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sky; like a wild animal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"twH~$","text_ar":"توحّش"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A, K.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada","text_ar":"اَبَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubuwdN","text_ar":"اُبُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a poet)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made use, in his verses, of words,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"phrases, strange, unusual, unfamiliar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"far from being intelligible,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as were not understood"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at first sight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on first consideration."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  [And perhaps from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abida","text_ar":"اَبِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense explained above, but more probably, I think, by the substitution of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abida","text_ar":"اَبِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor,"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, &c.,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadN","text_ar":"اَبَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was angry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, L, K;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amida","text_ar":"اَمِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabida","text_ar":"وَبِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wamida","text_ar":"وَمِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabida","text_ar":"عَبِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (T, L.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abida Ealayohi","text_ar":"اَبِدَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was angry with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["T","S","M","K","L","Msb","A","Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n10","headword_ar":"ابّد","root":"Abd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^obiydN","text_ar":"تَاْبِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered, perpetual."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) [See also the pass. part. n. below.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo A^afoEalo taA^obiydFA","text_ar":"لَمْ اَفْعَلْ تَاْبِيدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase used as though meaning ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo A=ti biA=bidapK","text_ar":"لَمْ ا=تِ بِا=بِدَةٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I did not a deed ever to be remembered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mentioned"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Ham p. 191.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, made"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a beast]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to take fright; to become wild,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sky."},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n12","headword_ar":"اـِبْدٌ","root":"Abd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibidN","text_ar":"اـِبِدٌ"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13","headword_ar":"اَبَدٌ","root":"Abd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in an absolute sense:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawiylN","text_ar":"طَوِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, and Mgh: [and this may be meant in the S &c. by the syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, q. v.:]) or, properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long time"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dhr Twyl","text_ar":"دهر طويل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is unlimited:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an extended space of time that is indivisible;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zamaAnu ka*aA","text_ar":"زَمَانُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": “ the time of such a thing,” but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadu ka*aA","text_ar":"اَبَدُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Er-Rághib:) [and generally,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"duration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"existence, without end; endless time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prospective eternity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azalN","text_ar":"اَزَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies “ time, or duration, &c., without beginning: ” (see the latter word for further explanations, &c.:) each of these significations may be meant by the explanation in the S and M and K, which is also given in the Msb: each correctly applies in particular instances:] pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=baAdN","text_ar":"ا=بَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ubuwdN","text_ar":"اُبُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaduwna","text_ar":"اَبَدُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which an ex. will be found below]: but the use of these pls. is restricted to particular cases, to signify portions of time, or to serve as corroboratives to the sing.: (MF:) as signifying an extended indivisible space of time, [or the like,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadN","text_ar":"اَبَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"should have neither dual nor pl.; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=baAdN","text_ar":"ا=بَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes said, when the sing. is restricted to denote a particular part, or portion, of the whole of that to which it applies, in like manner as a generic noun is restricted to a special and partial signification: some, however, have mentioned"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=baAdN","text_ar":"ا=بَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being post-classical; not of the language of the Arabs called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEarabu AlEarobaA='u","text_ar":"العَرَبُ العَرْبَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Er-Rághib.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAla AlA^abado EalaY lubado","text_ar":"طَالَ الاَبَدْ عَلَى لُبَدْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The time became long to Lubad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the last, and the longest of life, of Luk- mán's seven vultures, to the term of the life of which his own term of life was decreed to extend,] is a proverb applied to any thing that has been of long duration. (M.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"razaqaka A@ll~`hu EumurFA","text_ar":"رَزَقَكَ ا@للّٰهُ عُمُرًا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tawiyla AlA=baAdi baEiyda AlA=maAdi","text_ar":"طَوِيلَ الا=بَادِ بَعِيدَ الا=مَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May God grant thee a life long in duration"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"durations,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the pl. form being used not in its proper sense, but to give intensiveness of signification),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and remote in limit"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limits"},{"kind":"text","text":")]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna h`*aA fiY A=baAdi Ald~ahori","text_ar":"كَانَ هٰذَا فِى ا=بَادِ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This was a long time ago."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadN A=bidN","text_ar":"اَبَدٌ ا=بِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadN A^abiydN","text_ar":"اَبَدٌ اَبِيدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, TA,) meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAy^imN","text_ar":"دَايِمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in an intensive sense]; (TA;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an endless, period of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN daAhirN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ دَاهِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN dahiyrN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ دَهِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M.) [In each of these phrases, the latter word is added as a corroborative, or to give intensiveness to the signification.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liloA^abida","text_ar":"لِلْاَبِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^abidK","text_ar":"لِاَبِدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [in an intensive sense, as will be seen below,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^abida A^abadK","text_ar":"لِاَبِدَ اَبَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liA^abadi AlA^abadi","text_ar":"لِاَبَدِ الاَبَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to different recitals of a trad., signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To the end of time; for ever;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for ever and ever."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadFA","text_ar":"اَبَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an adv. n., of which the signification includes all future time; [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ever;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaT~u","text_ar":"قَطُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in relation to past time;] (El-Khafájee, El-Bedr Ed-Demámeenee, MF;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlA^abadi","text_ar":"عَلَى الاَبَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same. (TA.) [So, too, does"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abada","text_ar":"الاَبَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", unless used in a limited sense known to the hearer.] When you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^ukal~imuhu A^abadFA","text_ar":"لَا اُكَلِّمُهُ اَبَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", you mean, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not speak to him as long as I live,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"henceforth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ever;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will never speak to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,] from the time of your speaking to the end of your life. (Msb.) [In this case,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadFA","text_ar":"اَبَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"may also be considered as a mere corroborative. It is used in both these ways ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"llt~aA^osiysi","text_ar":"للتَّاْسِيسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lilt~awokiydi","text_ar":"لِلتَّوْكِيدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":") in affirmative as well as negative sentences. For exs. of its use in affirmative sentences, see the Kur xviii. 2 and iv. 60, &c.] One also says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEaluhu","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A=tiyhi","text_ar":"لَا ا=تِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada AlA=baAdi","text_ar":"اَبَدَ الا=بَادِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, M, A, K,) which, though of classical authority, is said to be no evidence of the use of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=bAd","text_ar":"ا=باد"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abadN","text_ar":"اَبَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a general way by the Arabs of the classical ages, as it is here added merely as a corroborative, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=zAl","text_ar":"ا=زال"},{"kind":"text","text":"is in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azala AlA=zaAli","text_ar":"اَزَلَ الا=زَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MF;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada AlA^abadiyna","text_ar":"اَبَدَ الاَبَدِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, K,) in which the latter word is not a rel. n., for if so it would be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abadiy~iyna","text_ar":"الاَبَدِيِّينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but app. a pl., (M,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araDuwna","text_ar":"اَرَضُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada AlA=bidiyna","text_ar":"اَبَدَ الا=بِدِينَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahora AlA=bidiyna","text_ar":"دَهْرَ الا=بِدِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada AlA^abadiy~api","text_ar":"اَبَدَ الاَبَدِيَّةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada AlA^abiydi","text_ar":"اَبَدَ الاَبِيدِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, S, M, A, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abiyda","text_ar":"اَبِيدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abiydi","text_ar":"الاَبِيدِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada AlA^abadi","text_ar":"اَبَدَ الاَبَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abada","text_ar":"اَبَدَ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":5},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahori","text_ar":"الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K; [in the T"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yada Ald~ahori","text_ar":"يَدَ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) all of which phrases are the same in meaning; (K;) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not come to him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA A=tyh","text_ar":"لا ا=تيه"},{"kind":"text","text":"may here mean the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lA AfElh","text_ar":"لا افعله"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during the endless space of all future times,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for ever and ever;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"εἰς αἰῶνα τῶν αἰώνων","text_ar":"εἰς αἰῶνα τῶν αἰώνων","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in seculum seculorum; in omne ævum;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the last word in every case being a corroborative. (MF.) ―         -b2-  Also, [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw A^abadK","text_ar":"ذُو اَبَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and (applied to a fem. n.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu A^abadK","text_ar":"ذَاتُ اَبَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lasting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"everlasting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~unyaA' A^amadN waAlA=xirapu A^abadN","text_ar":"الدُّنيَاء اَمَدٌ وَالا=خِرَةُ اَبَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The present state of existence is limited in duration, but the final state of existence is everlasting"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ('Obeyd Ibn-'Omeyr and L.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abadu","text_ar":"الاَبَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Everlasting;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. God; because He alone is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaAqiY AlA^abadiy~","text_ar":"البَاقِى الاَبَدِيّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Enduring without end"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cessation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the Muslims hold that all living creatures (even the angels) must die, and be raised again to life: or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Ancient without beginning."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Offspring that is a year old."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","TA","MF","A","T"]},{"entry_id":"n14","headword_ar":"اَبِدٌ","root":"Abd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unsocial, unsociable, unfamiliar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shy; like a wild animal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man, and to a young camel: (S, L:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibidN","text_ar":"اـِبِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a female slave, and to a she-ass, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shunning mankind, shy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=bidN","text_ar":"ا=بِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibidN","text_ar":"اـِبِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places."}],"source_refs":["S","L"]},{"entry_id":"n15","headword_ar":"اـِبِدٌ","root":"Abd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abidN","text_ar":"اَبِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  This word, (Lth, ISh, S, K,) said by Lth and ISh to be the only word of its measure heard from the Arabs except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilN","text_ar":"اـِبِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nikiHN","text_ar":"نِكِحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiTibN","text_ar":"خِطِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but Az says that he had not heard the last two from any person worthy of reliance, and that they are pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nikoHN","text_ar":"نِكْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiTobN","text_ar":"خِطْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilN","text_ar":"اـِبِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abidN","text_ar":"اَبِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibodN","text_ar":"اـِبْدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which are thought by Az to be dial. vars. of the first, (L,) applied to a female slave, and to a she-ass, signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Prolific; that breeds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brings forth, plentifully;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abidN","text_ar":"اَبِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abidapN","text_ar":"اَبِدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Málik, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibidapN","text_ar":"اـِبِدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Aboo-Málik, K,) applied to a she-camel, signify the same: (Aboo-Málik, K, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibidN","text_ar":"اـِبِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, ISh, L) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abidN","text_ar":"اَبِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L,) applied to a female slave, (M, L,) and to a she-ass, (Lth, ISh, M, L,) and to a mare, (M, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that brings forth every year;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, ISh, L;) or applied as a pl. to the female slave and the mare and the she-ass,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that breed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bring forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ibidaAni","text_ar":"الاـِبِدَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the female slave and the mare."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) In the following saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"Al~aAbijad~i *iY AlA_ibido \n                      \n                     \n                        lano yuqoliEa Aljad~u Aln~akido\n                      \n                     \n                        fiY kul~i maA EaAmK talido"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hard fortune will not depart save with the fortune"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is the necessary attendant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the possessor of the female slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as long as he possesses her, (or, if we take"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*Y","text_ar":"ذى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"save with the fortune of this female slave,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who every year"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"being redundant)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"brings forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAbd","text_ar":"الابد"},{"kind":"text","text":"means the female slave because her being prolific is an obstacle to prosperity, and is not good fortune; i. e., she only increases evil [and brings reproach upon her master by bearing him children; for the Arab in ancient times was considered as dishonoured by his having a child by a slave]. (S.) The Arabs also said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lano yaboluga Aljad~a Aln~akido","text_ar":"لَنْ يَبْلُغَ الجَدَّ النَّكِدْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA~a AlA^abido","text_ar":"الاَّ الاَبِدْ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nothing will attain to the object of removing hard fortune save female slaves and beasts or cattle which breed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bring forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L: [in the latter of which is added,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY kul~i EaAmK talido","text_ar":"فِى كُلِّ عَامٍ تَلِدْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in every year bringing forth."},{"kind":"text","text":"])"}],"source_refs":["Lth","ISh","S","K","L","M"]},{"entry_id":"n1942","headword_ar":"اَبَدٌّ","root":"bd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide between the thighs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of abundance of flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide between the arms;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the arms far from the sides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide between the shoulder-joints:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or (so in the K; but accord. to the S, “and”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large in make,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having one part far from another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide in the breast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Málik, T:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~aA='u","text_ar":"بَدَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) which also signifies a woman (M, L)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isokataAni","text_ar":"اـِسْكَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"labia majora of the vulva"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (M, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having their edges far apart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much flesh in the thighs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abad~N","text_ar":"الاَبَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The weaver,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, K,) because of the distance between his thighs. (M.) The following saying, (K,) quoted by J, from the rájiz Aboo-Nukheyleh Es-Saadee,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^alad~u yamo$iY mi$ayapa AlA^abad~i"},{"kind":"text","text":"is incorrect, and should be thus,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"bad~aA='u tamo$iY mi$oyapa AlA^abad~i"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman of large make, walking in the manner of the man of large make;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman wide between the thighs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (K;) for it is descriptive of a woman, as IB and Aboo-Sahl El-Harawee have observed before the author of the K. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also A horse [or any quadruped (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~a","text_ar":"بَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the fore legs far apart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the fore legs far from the sides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide between the legs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 348:) and a camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having the elbows far from the sides:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and the fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bad~aA='u","text_ar":"بَدَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a cow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having her fore legs far apart."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abad~u Alz~aniymu","text_ar":"الاَبَدُّ الزَّنِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aviymu","text_ar":"الرَّثِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) the former epithet being applied to him because his fore legs are far apart, and the latter because he is [often] alone. (M.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"katifN bad~aA='u","text_ar":"كَتِفٌ بَدَّا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A broad shoulder-blade, the sides of which are distant, one from another."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L.)"}],"source_refs":["ISk","S","M","K","T","L","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}